STEP 2 — Create Public and Private Subnets
What is a Subnet?

A subnet divides the VPC network.

You will create:

Type	CIDR
Public	10.0.1.0/24
Private	10.0.2.0/24
Create Public Subnet

Go:

Subnets

Click:

Create subnet

Fill:

Field	Value
VPC	Custom-VPC
Name	Public-Subnet
AZ	ap-south-1a
CIDR	10.0.1.0/24

Create subnet.

Create Private Subnet

Again click:

Create subnet

Fill:

Field	Value
Name	Private-Subnet
AZ	ap-south-1a
CIDR	10.0.2.0/24

Create.

STEP 3 — Create Internet Gateway (IGW)
Why IGW?

Internet Gateway allows:

internet access for public subnet

Without IGW:

no internet connectivity
Create IGW

Go:

Internet Gateways

Click:

Create internet gateway

Fill:

Field	Value
Name	Custom-IGW

Create.

Attach IGW to VPC

Select IGW.

Click:

Attach to VPC

Choose:

Custom-VPC

Attach.

